<paragraph id="390236EBD054FFE9C18AF924FAAB614D" blockId="6.[136,1451,1778,1876]" pageId="6" pageNumber="215">
Endemic to 
<collectingRegion id="FB79F809D054FFE9C01EF924FE5B6115" box="[284,391,1778,1804]" country="Australia" name="Tasmania" pageId="6" pageNumber="215">Tasmania</collectingRegion>
where it is occasional in sheltered microhabitats on highly siliceous, pre-Carboniferous, metamorphosed rocks in the south-west of the island. This species is closely related to 
<emphasis id="0BC9EAF9D054FFE9C55DF8C1FA776129" box="[1119,1451,1814,1840]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="215">
<taxonomicName id="FEBD4D68D054FFE9C55DF8C1FB2E6129" box="[1119,1266,1814,1840]" class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Xylographaceae" genus="Lambiella" kingdom="Fungi" pageId="6" pageNumber="215" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="applanata">L. applanata</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="FEBD4D68D054FFE9C5FCF8C1FA776129" box="[1278,1451,1814,1840]" class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Trapeliaceae" genus="Rimularia" kingdom="Fungi" pageId="6" pageNumber="215" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="globulispora">L. globulispora</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
and the newly described 
<taxonomicName id="FEBD4D68D054FFE9C09CF8EDFDC0614D" box="[414,540,1850,1876]" class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Xylographaceae" genus="Lambiella" kingdom="Fungi" pageId="6" pageNumber="215" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="plumbea">
<emphasis id="0BC9EAF9D054FFE9C09CF8EDFDC0614D" box="[414,540,1850,1876]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="215">L. plumbea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see 
<tableCitation id="743F0350D054FFE9C355F8ECFD75614D" box="[599,681,1850,1876]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="3.[136,224,159,183]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="TABLE 1. Comparison of salient features of the Lambiella applanata group. including the newly described L. plumbea." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/6DC26663D051FFECC18AFF49FA5766AE" pageId="6" pageNumber="215" tableUuid="6DC26663D051FFECC18AFF49FA5766AE">Table 1</tableCitation>
). A full description is provided by 
<bibRefCitation id="5D2C4B1AD054FFE9C530F8ECFAAF614D" author="Coppins, B. J. &amp; Kantvilas, G." box="[1074,1395,1850,1876]" pageId="6" pageNumber="215" pagination="35 - 48" refId="ref7270" refString="Coppins, B. J. &amp; Kantvilas, G. (2001) Four new species of Rimularia Nyl. (Agyriaceae). Bibliotheca Lichenologica 78: 35 - 48." type="journal article" year="2001">Coppins &amp; Kantvilas (2001)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
